{
  "stem": "27687.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And actually I made a little mistake before.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Gurs is by [FRENCH] and the Rivesaltes is by Perpignan.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So we could go to Perpignan.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They gave us a pass, and we could go to Perpignan.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The same people.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The same people, the French militia, but they were just the same.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They didn't care one way or another.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Even they were celebrating in their little house.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Almost every night they drank and they laughed and everything else, and they didn't care what the people were doing.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The reason nobody bothers us, there was no reason to run away.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't even think that anybody tried to run away at that time, because we had more food and somehow it was very close to Switzerland, and that was in that district there by the Mediterranean.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And somehow they sent in more stuff with the Red Cross.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so we had more-- we had more medicine and so on.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I didn't wanted to work anymore in the hospital, because I couldn't-- I couldn't live with that.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And so I became a [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] I-- we had-- we had a steam machine, and we steamed the clothing of the people periodically.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I had one guy, he was my boss, and he was about 10, 15 years older than I.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And so we worked pretty good together and, at the meantime, my father got sick with his eyes , and he got blind.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He had the cataract.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And so they took him to the hospital.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And my mother, she-- they took her away also to a Swiss hospital.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
